Importing the Data

link='https://github.com/Louisdebellis/PubPol-542-Group/raw/master/TeamData.RDS'
# a RDS file from the web needs:
myFile=url(link)

# reading in data:
TeamData=readRDS(file = myFile)

# reset indexes to R format:
row.names(TeamData)=NULL

Preparing Data

#Inspecting Data Set
str(TeamData[,c(2,4)])
## 'data.frame':    179 obs. of  2 variables:
##  $ HumanDevelopmentIndex  : num  0.953 0.944 0.939 0.938 0.936 0.935 0.933 0.933 0.932 0.931 ...
##  $ children_born_per_woman: num  1.85 1.56 1.77 1.97 1.45 2 1.88 1.19 0.83 1.78 ...
dfClus=TeamData[,c(2,4)]
row.names(dfClus)=TeamData$Country
head(dfClus)
##             HumanDevelopmentIndex children_born_per_woman
## Norway                      0.953                    1.85
## Switzerland                 0.944                    1.56
## Australia                   0.939                    1.77
## Ireland                     0.938                    1.97
## Germany                     0.936                    1.45
## Iceland                     0.935                    2.00
# Setting seed for replicability of results
set.seed(999) 
library(cluster)
dfClus_D=cluster::daisy(x=dfClus,)

Clustering: Partitioning (Pam)

#Cluster Pam
NumCluster=4
res.pam = pam(x=dfClus_D,k = NumCluster,cluster.only = F)
#Adding results to data frame
TeamData$pam=as.factor(res.pam$clustering)
#Table Clusters
table(TeamData$pam)
## 
##  1  2  3  4 
## 61 54 31 33
#Evaulating Results
library(factoextra)
## Loading required package: ggplot2

fviz_silhouette(res.pam)

Clustering: Hierarchizing(Divisive)

#Running Diana
res.diana= hcut(dfClus_D, k = NumCluster,
                 hc_func='diana',
                 hc_method = "ward.D")

TeamData$dia=as.factor(res.diana$cluster)
#Report table of clusters
table(TeamData$dia)
## 
##  1  2  3  4 
## 95 43 27 14
#Evaluate Results of Diana
#Dendogram
fviz_dend(res.diana,k=NumCluster, cex = 0.7, horiz = T)

#Average Sulhouettes
fviz_silhouette(res.diana)

Clustering: Hierarchizing(Agglomerative)

# Running Agnes
res.agnes= hcut(dfClus_D, k = NumCluster,isdiss=T,
                 hc_func='agnes',
                 hc_method = "ward.D2")
TeamData$agn=as.factor(res.agnes$cluster)
table(TeamData$agn)
## 
##  1  2  3  4 
## 94 50 27  8

#Dendogram

CLustering: Densiity-Based Clustering

#Input the distance and the minimal number of neighbors that form a cluster.
library(dbscan)
#minNeighs> num cols in data
minNeighs=4
kNNdistplot(dfClus_D, k = minNeighs)
abline(h=.2, col = "red", lty=2)

#Setting min distance
distance=0.2
res.db = dbscan::dbscan(dfClus_D, eps=distance, 
                     minPts=minNeighs)
#Tabling cluster results
res.db
## DBSCAN clustering for 179 objects.
## Parameters: eps = 0.2, minPts = 4
## The clustering contains 5 cluster(s) and 5 noise points.
## 
##   0   1   2   3   4   5 
##   5 143  15   4   6   6 
## 
## Available fields: cluster, eps, minPts
#Saving result
TeamData$db=as.factor(res.db$cluster)
#Prparing a bidimensional map
projectedData = cmdscale(dfClus_D, k=2)
#Save coordinates to original data frame:
TeamData$dim1 = projectedData[,1]
TeamData$dim2 = projectedData[,2]
#Seeing the map
base= ggplot(data=TeamData,
             aes(x=dim1, y=dim2,
                 label=Country)) 
base + geom_text(size=2)

Comparing Clustering: (Pam, Diana, and Agnes)

#Plot results for Hierarchical Agnes
agnPlot=base + labs(title = "AGNES") + geom_point(size=2,
                                              aes(color=agn),
                                              show.legend = F) 
#Plot Results for PAM
pamPlot=base + labs(title = "PAM") + geom_point(size=2,
                                              aes(color=pam),
                                              show.legend = F) 

#Plot results from Hierarchical DIANA

diaPlot=base + labs(title = "DIANA") + geom_point(size=2,
                                              aes(color=dia),
                                              show.legend = F) 
pamPlot=base + labs(title = "PAM") + geom_point(size=2,
                                              aes(color=pam),
                                              show.legend = F)
#Compare Visually
library(ggpubr)
## Loading required package: magrittr
ggarrange(pamPlot, agnPlot, diaPlot,ncol = 3)

#Plot results from DBSCAN
library(ggrepel)
dbPlot= base + labs(title = "DBSCAN") + geom_point(aes(color=db),
                                               show.legend = T) 
dbPlot

#Plot results from DBSCAN with and without outliers
LABEL=ifelse(TeamData$db==0,TeamData$Country,"")

dbPlot + geom_text_repel(aes(label=LABEL))

Histogram Plotting of Cluster (Hierarchizing: divisive)

#Plot by HDI
ggplot(TeamData) +
  geom_histogram(aes(x=HumanDevelopmentIndex, fill=dia),binwidth=0.05) +
  facet_wrap(~dia,nc=2) + theme_gray(base_size = 14)

#Plot by TFR                                              
ggplot(TeamData) +
  geom_histogram(aes(x=children_born_per_woman, fill=dia),binwidth=0.05) +
  facet_wrap(~dia,nc=2) + theme_gray(base_size = 14)

Regression

# hypotheses:
hypo1=formula(children_born_per_woman~ HumanDevelopmentIndex)
hypo2=formula(children_born_per_woman~ HumanDevelopmentIndex + Continent)
colsNeeded=c('children_born_per_woman','HumanDevelopmentIndex','Continent')
DataRegGauss=TeamData[,colsNeeded]
#Rename indexes by country
row.names(DataRegGauss)=TeamData$Country
# results
gauss1=glm(hypo1,data = DataRegGauss,family = 'gaussian')
gauss2=glm(hypo2,data = DataRegGauss,family = 'gaussian')
summary(gauss1)
